latestPosts.caption:
A Tangerine Princess 🍊🧡

Every styling assignment teaches you something new. I was very keen that Rhea should wear a geometric print on her choodha but she convinced me that a monotone would be more “her”.
PS: it’s also Rishi’s favourite colour cause of his love for butter chicken 😂

The veil? Customised from scratch to add the oomph factor to this whole look. Stay tuned for the story!

Styled by: @styledbyrashikapur

latestPosts.caption:
Family styling 🤎🧿

Dhol night was all about patialas, pegs and pops of color! 

Dressed the family in classic black with pops of color for a regal yet fun dhol night look! ✨ Added statement shawls for the men to keep it elegant, while the bride shined in a bright ensemble to stand out. 

Mother of the bride wore a zardosi flared kurta with salwar and sister of the bride (me) wore a peplum kurta set in black with gold sequence. 

A perfect blend of tradition, royalty, and celebration!

Bride’s outfit: @ameerandesign Jewels: @kashajewellery 
Bride’s sister’s outfit: @debyaniandco Jewels: @birdhichand 
Bride’s mom’s outfit: kurta by @dareaab_by_soniakmahajan and salwar and dupatta by @sulbhaandseemaofficial Jewels: @kashajewellery 
Men’s outfits: Custom
Glam for Rhea and me: @shradhaluthra 
Photos: @weddingnama

latestPosts.caption:
Some love stories never end, they just get passed down❤️🧿

When I stumbled upon my mom’s wedding photo I knew I wanted to do something for my sister @rheamarwah’s wedding with it. My mom and Rhea both loved the idea and @ameerandesign transformed it into the most stunning Sharara by using the booties and borders all across and even using some of the borders on the kurta. We paired it with a firozi dupatta to add another offbeat touch to it. 

This outfit was pure love! 🥺

Styled by: @styledbyrashikapur 
Outfit: @ameerandesign 
MUA: @shradhaluthra 
Jewellery: @kashajewellery
